      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنِ اَلْمَرْأَةِ تَخْرُجُ إِلَى مَكَّةَ بِغَيْرِ وَلِيٍّ فَقَالَ «لاَ بَأْسَ تَخْرُجُ مَعَ قَوْمٍ ثِقَاتٍ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2910 - It was narrated from Mu'awiyah ibn Ammar, who said:\nI asked Abu Abdullah (as) about a woman traveling to Mecca without a guardian.\nImam (as) said: \"There is no harm if she travels with trustworthy people.\""
        ]
      }
